{{Use dmy dates|date=June 2018}} {{Use Indian English|date=June 2018}} {{Infobox Museum |name = Indira Gandhi Rashtriya Manav Sangrahalaya |image = Parol Himalayan Village gate.JPG |caption = Indira Gandhi Rashtriya Manav Sangrahalaya |coordinates = {{coord|23.232279|77.37761|display=inline}} |established = |dissolved = |location = [[Bhopal]] , [[India]] |type = [[Anthropology museums]] |visitors = |director = |publictransit = |website = [http://www.igrms.gov.in www.igrms.gov.in] }}
[[File:Rabari house.jpg|thumb|right|Rabari house]] '''Indira Gandhi Rashtriya Manav Sangrahalaya''' ('''IGRMS''') or '''National Museum of Humankind''' or '''Museum of Man''' is an [[anthropology]] museum located in [[Bhopal]], [[India]], to present an integrated story of the [[evolution of man]] and culture with special reference to India. It spreads over an area of about 200 acres on the Shyamla Hills in the city.<ref>[http://igrms.com/ IGRMS website]</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=International Museum Day to be celebrated on May 18 |url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2013-04-27/bhopal/38861014_1_gandhi-rashtriya-manav-sangrahalaya-director-igrms-exhibition |newspaper=The Times of India|date=27 Apr 2013 |accessdate=12 May 2013}}</ref> This museum depicts the story of mankind in time and space. Located on Bhopal's upper lake, 'Rashtriya Manav Sangrahalaya' can be accessed either from Lake View Road or from another road near Demonstration School. IGRMS has a few permanent exhibitions, broadly categorized as a) Open-exhibitions, b) Indoor galleries (Veethi-Sankul and Bhopal Gallery) and c) Periodical/ Temporary exhibitions. It also has other exhibitions categorized as 1. Online exhibitions, 2. Travelling exhibitions, 3. Special exhibitions and 4. Ongoing exhibitions.
The following open-air exhibitions partially developed and opened for the public: Tribal Habitat. Coastal Village, Desert Village, Himalayan Village, Mythological Trail, Traditional Technology park.
The museum also has a regional centre for the [[South India]] region at [[Mysore]] in Karnataka.<ref>{{cite news |title=Seminar on tribal and analogous culture |url=http://www.hindu.com/2010/08/02/stories/2010080253990300.htm |newspaper=The Hindu |date=2 Aug 2010 |accessdate=12 May 2013}}</ref>
