{{short description|The study of aquatic plants and algae that live in seawater of the open ocean and the littoral zone, along shorelines of the intertidal zone, and in brackish water of estuaries.}} {{ocean habitat topics}} '''Marine botany''' is the study of [[aquatic plants]] and [[algae]] that live in [[seawater]] of the open [[ocean]] and the [[littoral zone]], along [[shoreline]]s of the [[intertidal zone]], and in [[brackish water]] of [[estuary|estuaries]].
It is a branch of [[marine biology]] and [[botany]].
==Marine ecology== [[Marine ecology]] and marine botany include: * [[Benthic zone]] * [[Coral reef]] * [[Kelp forest]]s * [[Mangroves]] * [[Phytoplankton]] * [[Salt marsh]] * [[Sea grass]] * [[Seaweed]]
==See also== * [[Aquatic plants]] * [[:Category:Aquatic ecology|Aquatic ecology]] * "[[Aquatic Botany]]" — ''scientific journal'' * [[Phycology]] — ''study of algae'' * [[:Category:Marine botany|Index: Marine botany]]
